  "text": "The Kubernetes scheduler plugin framework architecture is implemented across several key files in the kubernetes/kubernetes repository v1.32.0:\n\n**Framework Interface Definitions** (pkg/scheduler/framework/interface.go):\nThe core plugin interfaces are defined here, including the base Plugin interface (line 443) and all extension point plugins: FilterPlugin (line 540), ScorePlugin (line 607), BindPlugin (line 673), PreFilterPlugin, PostFilterPlugin, PreScorePlugin, ReservePlugin, PreBindPlugin, PostBindPlugin, and PermitPlugin. The Framework interface (line 686) manages the set of plugins and orchestrates the scheduling cycle. The Handle interface provides data and tools for plugins, while PluginsRunner abstracts operations to run plugins during scheduling.\n\n**Data Types** (pkg/scheduler/framework/types.go):\nContains essential data structures like Status (for plugin return values), CycleState (for sharing state across plugins in a scheduling cycle), and NodeInfo (representing a single node's information).\n\n**Scheduling Orchestration** (pkg/scheduler/schedule_one.go):\nThe ScheduleOne method (line 65) on the Scheduler struct drives the scheduling cycle for a single pod, orchestrating the PreFilter, Filter, PostFilter, PreScore, Score, Reserve, Permit, PreBind, and Bind phases.\n\n**Top-Level Scheduler** (pkg/scheduler/scheduler.go):\nDefines the Scheduler struct (line 66) which watches for unscheduled pods and attempts to schedule them. The Run method (line 464) begins watching and scheduling, starting the scheduleOne loop in a dedicated goroutine.\n\n**Framework Runtime Implementation** (pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/framework.go):\nContains the frameworkImpl struct (line 52) which implements the Framework interface. This is the runtime component responsible for initializing and running scheduler plugins. Key methods include RunFilterPlugins (line 872) and RunScorePlugins (line 1112), which invoke the configured filter and score plugins respectively with proper error handling and metrics recording.\n\n**Plugin Registry** (pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/registry.go):\nThe NewInTreeRegistry function (line 47) builds a registry with all built-in plugins including dynamicresources, imagelocality, tainttoleration, nodename, nodeports, nodeaffinity, podtopologyspread, nodeunschedulable, noderesources, volumebinding, volumerestrictions, volumezone, nodevolumelimits, interpodaffinity, queuesort, defaultbinder, defaultpreemption, and schedulinggates.\n\n**Plugin Registry Runtime** (pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/registry.go):\nProvides the Registry type and related functions for managing plugin registration and instantiation.\n\nThe scheduling flow chain is: Scheduler.Run → ScheduleOne → RunFilterPlugins/RunScorePlugins (via frameworkImpl). Plugins are registered through NewInTreeRegistry and can be extended via the out-of-tree registry mechanism."
}

